&lt;p&gt;At Tend, we’re reimagining what dentistry can be. As an Assistant Studio Manager, you’ll support the Studio Manager in running day-to-day operations while keeping our focus on delivering “Dental Done Differently.” This role blends hospitality, operational excellence, and team leadership to ensure both our guests and our studio team members feel cared for every step of the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a floating position supporting multiple tend studios&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Studio Manager in daily operations, including scheduling, inventory, and opening/closing routines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage front desk operations and lead the front desk team through interviewing, training, coaching, and performance feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a strong understanding of insurance, schedule management, and treatment planning to support studio performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver financial presentations and track results to help meet revenue goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with the Studio Manager and broader teams (member experience, revenue cycle) to support a seamless guest journey.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and lead specialty treatment days (orthodontics and oral surgery).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee ordering of supplies, including Amazon shipments, and manage studio inventory.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize provider scheduling to balance team efficiency and guest needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive patient (member) retention through outreach and follow-ups for unscheduled treatment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide warm, consistent hospitality for every guest — whether in-studio, by phone, or by email.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the entire clinical and non-clinical team to ensure high-quality guest and team experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take initiative to identify and complete tasks without direct supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Tend, our values guide everything we do — how we care for our guests, how we work together, and how we grow as a team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tend Values&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tend to Others&lt;/strong&gt;: You create an environment where patients and teammates feel cared for, and you help the team succeed by driving meaningful results.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Be Brave Enough to Lead&lt;/strong&gt;: You’re not afraid to make decisions or take action when it’s needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Savor the Ride&lt;/strong&gt;: You bring positivity that keeps the team engaged and guests smiling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Embrace Our Differences&lt;/strong&gt;: You value and respect people from all backgrounds and perspectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rooted in Growth&lt;/strong&gt;: You seek feedback, stay curious, and grow from every experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role-Based Competencies&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow Your Team&lt;/strong&gt;: You coach, train, and support others so they can succeed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stay Organized&lt;/strong&gt;: You plan and prioritize to keep the studio running smoothly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Think Ahead&lt;/strong&gt;: You see the bigger picture and adjust priorities to keep the studio on track.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Have&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of experience in a healthcare, hospitality, or service management role (dental experience strongly preferred).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading or coaching a team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong organizational and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills across phone, email, and in-person interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li

